text: Garden Island ferry wharf is located on the southern side of Sydney Harbour. It serves the Royal Australian Navy's Heritage Centre, Garden Island. ==Wharves & services== Garden Island wharf is served by Sydney Ferries Double Bay services operated by First Fleet and SuperCat class ferries. It is only open between 10:00 and 16:00 coinciding with the opening hours of the Royal Australian Navy's Heritage Centre, Garden Island.Where is it? Royal Australian Navy Heritage Centre The Captain Cook Cruises Hop On/Hop Off Sydney Harbour ferry service operates via Garden Island wharf. ==References== ==External links== *Garden Island Wharf at Transport for New South Wales (Archived 12 June 2019) Category:Ferry wharves in Sydney Category:Garden Island (New South Wales)
